<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1455,2019]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,319,1527,1552]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
MALE. Mandible without pre-apical lower tooth, sensillae chaetica in lower margin of mandible absent. Antennal scrobe not projected forward. Eye weakly pilose. Ocelli large. Vertex convex in dorsal view. Parapsidal furrow shallower than notaulus. Lateral of propodeum areolate. Paramere arched slightly ventrad, large and 2.0 × longer than basiparamere. Aedeagus inner margin almost straight and inner lobe membranous and setose. Apodeme base rounded, not dilated. FEMALE unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="31" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" type="description">
