<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1455,2019]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis box="[197,260,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">Color</emphasis>
. Head, 
<taxonomicName box="[347,465,1745,1768]" class="Crustacea" family="Crustacea" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea" pageId="11" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">mesosoma</taxonomicName>
and coxae dark castaneous nearly black. Trochanters, fore and metafemora dark castaneous. Metasoma dark castaneous with apex castaneous. Scape, pedicel, flagellum, mandible, tegula, protibia, tarsi castaneous. Palpi and wing venation light castaneous. Wings subhyaline.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1455,2019]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,1423,2024]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="30" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
