). Mandible (
<figureCitation box="[528,664,1851,1875]" captionStart="FIGURES 7 – 18" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1085,1108]" captionTargetBox="[184,1407,198,1061]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[178,1409,193,1064]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 7 – 18. Mandible. 7 – 9. Epyris afer Ƥ, lectotype. 7. Frontal view; 8. Ventral view; 9. Dorsal view. 10 – 12. E. afer 3, paralectotype. 10. Frontal view; 11. Ventral view; 12. Dorsal view. 13 – 15. E. enerterus sp. nov. Ƥ, holotype. 13. Frontal view; 14. Ventral view; 15. Dorsal view. 16 – 18. E. penatii sp. nov. 3, holotype. 16. Frontal view; 17. Ventral view; 18. Dorsal view. (Scale bar = 200 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204626/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="28">
Figs. 
<number box="[593,664,1851,1875]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" value="17.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="16.0">16–18</number>
</figureCitation>
) apex wider than base, with five sharpened apical teeth, two lower wider than others, pre-apical lower tooth absent; sensillae chaetica in lower margin of mandible absent. Clypeus longer than wide, median lobe angulate; median carina present; apex of clypeus without setae; lateral lobe reduced. Transversal section of scape cylindrical; first four antennal segments ratio 
<number box="[979,1011,1960,1984]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" value="16.0">16</number>
: 
<number box="[1015,1031,1960,1984]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" value="6.0">6</number>
: 
<number box="[1035,1067,1960,1984]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" value="10.0">10</number>
: 
<number box="[1072,1101,1960,1984]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" value="11.0">11</number>
, segment III 
<number box="[1247,1282,1960,1984]" pageId="11" pageNumber="28" value="1.7">1.7</number>
× longer than thick; antennal sensillae not visible. Antennal scrobe not projected, dorsally carinate. Toruli distant from each other 
<number box="[151,186,1423,1447]" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" value="2.2">2.2</number>
× their diameter. Eye almost reaching upper mandibular condyle, prominent, weakly pilose. Frons coriaceous; punctures large and deep, separated from each other by 1.0 × their diameter. WH 
<number box="[1067,1102,1459,1483]" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" value="1.1">1.1</number>
× LH; WF 
<number box="[1234,1269,1459,1483]" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" value="1.3">1.3</number>
× HE; WF 
<number box="[1401,1436,1459,1483]" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" value="0.6">0.6</number>
× WH; OOL 
<number box="[297,332,1495,1519]" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" value="0.8">0.8</number>
× WOT; VOL 
<number box="[501,536,1495,1519]" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" value="0.5">0.5</number>
× HE; distance of posterior ocellus to vertex crest 
<number box="[1099,1134,1495,1519]" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" value="0.5">0.5</number>
× 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15671" box="[1162,1227,1495,1519]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15671" name="Agriculture and Agri-Food Canada" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">
<collectingCountry box="[1162,1227,1495,1519]" name="Iceland" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">DAO</collectingCountry>
</collectionCode>
. Ocelli large, frontal angle of ocellar triangle right. Temple posteriorly convergent in dorsal view. Vertex slightly convex in dorsal view. Crest without setae. Occipital carina present dorsally and ventrally. Gena flattened (
<figureCitation box="[1202,1274,1567,1591]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1904,1927]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,195,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Head. 1. Epyris afer Ƥ, lectotype, dorsal view. 2 – 3. E. enerterus sp. nov. Ƥ, holotype. 2. Dorsal view; 3. Ventral view. 4. E. afer 3, paralectotype, dorsal view. 5 – 6. E. penatii sp. nov. 3, holotype. 5. Dorsal view; 6. Ventral view. (Scale bar = 200 µm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/204625/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="30">
Fig. 
<number box="[1258,1274,1567,1591]" pageId="13" pageNumber="30" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypostomal carina triangular and polished.
</paragraph>
